dataStructure.name: sid.org.tmforum.tip.resource.res.log.tip.nrf.MatrixFlowDomain
dataStructure.description:
This object class is contained within a Managed Element (ME) and represents a grouping of assigned Connectionless Port Termination Points (CPTPs). See R_TMF518_NRF_I_0047 and R_TMF518_NRF_I_0048.

This entity is optional

This entity is extendable

This entity generates Object Creation notifications

This entity generates Object Deletion notifications

This entity generates Object Discovery notifications

This entity generates Attribute Value Change notifications.
dataStructure.label: MatrixFlowDomain

child.name: isFlexible
child.description:
This attribute indicates whether the MFD is fixed and cannot be configured by the NMS (= False) or is flexible (= True).

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is invariant

This attribute is optional

This attribute is AVC disabled
child.label: isFlexible

child.name: tmdState
child.description:
This attribute contains the state of consistency between a TP and its associated egress TransmissionDescriptor.

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional

This attribute is AVC enabled
child.label: tmdState

child.name: transmissionParameterList
child.description:
This attribute contains the technology-specific parameters associated with the different connectionless layers that are supported by the MFD. Refer to to chapter Connectionless Technology Parameters of the attached supporting document SD1-16_LayeredParameters for details of the currently defined Transmission Parameter

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional

This attribute is AVC enabled
child.label: transmissionParameterList
